    <tal:block metal:fill-slot="main-content-title">
      <h1>About <small>The story goes ...</small></h1>
    </tal:block>
    <tal:block metal:fill-slot="main-content">
      <div class="span10">
        <p><strong>Almir</strong> is a <a href="http://www.bacula.org">bacula</a> web interface for administrators. It is designed with simplicity in mind, although backup management is never simple.</p>

        <p>It is named by <strong>Almir Karič</strong>, a fellow developer from <strong>Slovenia</strong>, whose dream was to live in San Francisco. Two years after he moved, he died in a car crash. This is his gift for ethernity.</p>

        <p><strong>Almir</strong> is thus open source software licensed under <strong>GPL v3</strong>, developed by <a href="http://www.domenkozar.com">Domen Kožar</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </tal:block>

